                description: "A simulation tool that assesses household vulnerabilities and maps social protection gaps by modelling demographics, income, expenditure, and scheme access over time.",
                themes: ["Energy & Climate"],
                time: 4, workload: 4, budget: 3,
                whatIsIt: "E-QLT is a simulation tool designed to assess vulnerabilities and integrate social protection measures for households. By analysing factors such as demography, income, expenditure, and access to social protection measures, it offers insights into a household\u2019s vulnerability level and pathways for resilience. Uses system dynamic modelling to simulate a household\u2019s state and calculate a Social Protection Score across health, education, and finance dimensions.",
                whyExists: "Vulnerabilities are temporal and dynamic, forming an intricate web across finance, caste, gender, education, health, and social capital. Schemes and policies exist to help families tackle vulnerabilities, but it\u2019s difficult to map how different schemes stitch together social protection for a particular household. E-QLT helps by quantifying dynamic vulnerabilities and scheme effectiveness.",
                involves: ["Collection of household-level data through CSOs", "System dynamic modelling to simulate household state over 10 years", "Calculation of Social Protection Score (Health, Education, Finance)", "Analysis of data in partnership with CSOs", "Integration of E-QLT within organisations"],
