                description: "A storytelling tool that builds dialogue between groups, helping communities share experiences, identify shared risks, and surface common issues for policy input.",
                themes: ["Governance & Policy"],
                time: 2, workload: 1, budget: 1,
                whatIsIt: "Ondu Kathe Keli (\u2018Listen to a Story\u2019) is a tool to build dialogue where individuals from different groups share their experiences, recognise commonalities and diversities, and identify shared risks and values. Storytellers visit themed booths where listeners collect stories and assign coloured blocks (challenge or support). The blocks fill a collective jar, visualising the community\u2019s shared experience.",
                whyExists: "Stories provide rich qualitative data about people\u2019s lived experiences \u2014 their needs, preferences, and challenges. When shared collectively, two outcomes emerge: a sense of collective understanding built on shared experiences, and a pool of common issues that can inform policy decisions.",
