                whatIsIt: "The Handbook on Urban Services for Small Cities in Uttar Pradesh is a visually driven, practice-oriented guide on sustainable development for transitioning city-regions. It covers streets and public spaces, natural environment, solid waste, liquid waste, and water systems. Through focus principles and best practices, it aims to inform government functionaries, local communities, planners, and builders to co-design right-sized, contextual, and scalable urban service provision. Developed with IIT Bombay, Biome Environmental Solutions, The Urban Lab, Saahas, and Lemnion Green Solutions.",
                whyExists: "Small cities in UP face persistent challenges in urban service delivery. Planning frameworks and infrastructure investments are often borrowed from large city contexts, resulting in systems misaligned with local demand, institutional capacity, and financial realities.",
