                description: "A community-led decentralised composting initiative that transforms organic waste from temples and public parks into compost, reducing landfill dependency and creating a circular economy at the ward level.",
                themes: ["Waste & Circular Economy"],
                time: 4, workload: 4, budget: 3,
                whatIsIt: "The Greens & Browns Story by Zero Waste Collective Malleswaram is a community-led environmental initiative defining a new standard for neighbourhood sustainability. It reduces landfill waste through decentralisation of solid waste management at the ward level, creating a circular economy. The project transforms biodegradable waste from temples and parks into valuable compost through on-site segregation, micro-plastic removal, mechanical shredding, and composting. Supported by Brigade Foundation, SWMRT, Malleswaram Social, Sampige Foundation, and Prakruthi Shaale.",
                whyExists: "Despite the spiritual significance of temple offerings like flowers and leaves, the organic waste generated is often dumped indiscriminately, leading to methane emissions, pest issues, and increased dependency on municipal landfills. The project addresses the landfill and emissions crisis, systemic pressure on municipalities, linear waste patterns (shifting to circular economy), and lack of community stewardship by providing a structured platform for volunteering and hands-on environmental action.",
                involves: ["On-site segregation and composting at 14 active temples and public parks in Malleswaram", "Structured community volunteering including Wednesday Plog and sorting sessions", "Mechanical shredding of organic material with dedicated equipment", "Local transit to Panchavati processing hub (700m) \u2014 eliminating long-haul transport emissions", "Composting at dedicated stations (Temple Leaf-Flower Composting Station and mesh-bin structures)", "Education and outreach with tours, workshops, and annual volunteering calendar for 25,000+ students", "Ward-level scaling by integrating multiple worship places and community spaces"],
                whereDone: "Malleswaram, Bengaluru (BBMP Ward 65). Nandi Theertha Temple (1st Temple Street) \u2014 Shredding Station. Kempegowda Tower Park (Sadashivanagar Park) \u2014 Shredding & Processing Station. Panchavati (15th Cross) \u2014 Processing Station. 14+ temples including Kadu Malleswara, Sai Baba Temple, Gangamma Temple, Lakshminarasimha Swamy Temple, and others.",
                impact: "LIVE for 700+ days. Diverts 1.10 tons of waste per month from landfills. 5+ tons of compost harvested. 3,000+ participants engaged. 1,700+ volunteering hours. Weekly collection peaks of 400 kg (March 2026). Daily collection peak of 96.2 kg. Operating with 15+ partners across the Malleswaram cluster.",
                whatsNeeded: "Host sites: access to temples, public parks, and high-footfall community spaces. On-site composting stations with space for shredders and segregated collection bins. Volunteer platforms for residents, youth, and devotees. Educational partnerships with 20+ schools and colleges. Collaboration with BBMP and civic organisations. Community support to purchase and reuse harvested compost (closing the loop).",
